    "Documents Referenced by This Report": {
      "DOCUMENT_NAME_OR_NO": [
        "4.3.3 Elements of Prose",
        "4.3.4 Objectives of Teaching Prose",
        "3.5 Writing Skills",
        "3.6 Introduction to Phonetics",
        "5.5.10 Lesson Plan Format Based on CCE",
        "5.6 Micro-teaching",
        "Unit 2 Different Approaches/Theories to Language Learning and Teaching"
      ],
      "DOCUMENTS_DESCRIPTION": [
        "Prose is organized in paragraphs and they have important elements of fiction. They are plot, character, theme, setting, the point of view, style, and figures of speech.",
        "Prose teaching is meant for language learning. It is through prose teaching that learners learn reading comprehension, pronunciation, vocabulary, content words, and grammar.",
        "Writing is one of the most important productive skills in language teaching and learning. Writing is also an essential part of the process of language production.",
        "Phonetics is the scientific study and classification of sounds. The English language has 44 sounds, which consist of 20 vowel sounds and 24 consonant sounds.",
        "The lesson plan format based on CCE involves pre-reading, reading, post-reading, and editing activities for prose, poetry, and story lessons.",
        "Micro-teaching is a teacher training technique which aims at modifying teachers' behavior according to specific objectives. It is a controlled practice that makes it possible to concentrate on teaching behavior in the learner-teacher training program.",
        "This unit discusses various methods and approaches used in language teaching, starting from the Grammar-Translation method to the Natural approach, including traditional and humanistic approaches."
      ]
    }
  },
